{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/tips-to-make-vim-shown-white-space-characters","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"d3adcbdf-d4f1-5df4-8712-a7ddd94239e2","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/4b190/vim-lcs.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/8ac56/vim-lcs.webp 240w,\n/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/d3be9/vim-lcs.webp 480w,\n/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/d00b9/vim-lcs.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/09b79/vim-lcs.jpg 240w,\n/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/7cc5e/vim-lcs.jpg 480w,\n/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/4b190/vim-lcs.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/4b190/vim-lcs.jpg\"\n            alt=\"example\"\n            title=\"example\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\nWhile editing text files with <strong>vi/vim</strong>, we often need the white space characters to be shown, like ‘\\t’ (tabulation), ‘\\n’ (end of line), and ’ ‘(space) to confirm the file syntax. How to show these characters in different ways? You may just use the following vim command,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"vim\"><pre class=\"language-vim\"><code class=\"language-vim\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token keyword\">set</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">list</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>By default, ‘\\t’ is shown as ‘^I’, ‘\\n’ is shown as ’$’, and ’ ’ is kept not changed. You may also want to customize the representations, this could be configured via the <strong>listchars/lcs</strong> option, e.g,</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"vim\"><pre class=\"language-vim\"><code class=\"language-vim\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token keyword\">set</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">lcs</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token keyword\">tab</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>trail<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token builtin\">eol</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>space<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>~</code></pre></div>\n<p>You may refer to the vim help documents (section listchars) for more details.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"vim\"><pre class=\"language-vim\"><code class=\"language-vim\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token keyword\">help</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">listchars</span></code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/tips-to-make-vim-shown-white-space-characters","tagSlugs":["/tag/linux-system/","/tag/vim/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2012-01-20T21:05:00.000Z","description":"instructions about how to install software and set up a routed wireless AP with Pi 4B.","tags":["Linux System","Vim"],"title":"Tips to Make Vim Shown White Space Characters","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/f13a0c006860e522cb907ddfc4b4cf91/vim-lcs.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/tips-to-make-vim-shown-white-space-characters"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}